WEBVTT

00:02.393 --> 00:05.396
[ Engine revving ]

00:17.974 --> 00:19.584
Solider: Up.

00:19.628 --> 00:22.935
Lila: He killed himself, Ethan,
just like your brother did.

00:22.979 --> 00:26.287
Ethan: What happened?
Damon:
None of your damn business!

00:26.330 --> 00:28.289
Robert killed us all
that day.

00:28.332 --> 00:31.205
And now you have to live with it. [ Echoes]

00:31.248 --> 00:32.815
I don't anymore.

00:32.858 --> 00:34.121
No!
[ Gunshot ]

00:34.164 --> 00:36.036
Ethan: Three people
in the same unit

00:36.079 --> 00:38.342
have taken their own lives, and
the first one was my brother.

00:38.386 --> 00:40.736
Willis! Willis!

00:40.779 --> 00:42.738
You reopened old wounds.

00:42.781 --> 00:45.915
What's hard is you.
I'm done.

00:45.958 --> 00:48.526
I don't have any sons left.

00:48.570 --> 00:50.180
-Hey.
-What's going on?

00:50.224 --> 00:51.877
I called you three times.

00:51.921 --> 00:54.315
[ Siren wailing ]
Yeah, I know.

00:54.358 --> 00:56.752
Ethan, that was a lot
for anyone --

00:56.795 --> 00:59.537
the funeral, Damon,
your dad.

00:59.581 --> 01:01.539
I'm fine.

01:01.583 --> 01:03.150
I thought
you just might need...

01:03.193 --> 01:07.328
A shoulder to cry on?
No. Not really my style.

01:07.371 --> 01:09.591
Have a good shift.

01:09.634 --> 01:11.158
[ Siren continues wailing ]

01:11.201 --> 01:14.378
And now he's just...gone.

01:14.422 --> 01:17.294
My husband was my...

01:17.338 --> 01:20.036
everything.

01:20.080 --> 01:22.734
He was a hero.

01:22.778 --> 01:26.086
♪♪

01:26.129 --> 01:30.525
As a cop, he --
he saved so many lives.

01:32.179 --> 01:35.095
But when he needed
a doctor to save him...

01:38.054 --> 01:41.318
[ Voice breaking ]
...no one did.

01:41.362 --> 01:43.320
[ Crying ]

01:43.364 --> 01:47.194
I'm sorry I'm late.
Hey. Rox. Are you ready for
your ride-along?

01:47.237 --> 01:49.065
-Yes.
-Ride-along?

01:49.109 --> 01:51.154
-Why are you in scrubs?
-I am trailing Dr. Rorish today

01:51.198 --> 01:53.287
to brush up
on my diagnostic skills.

01:53.330 --> 01:54.723
Is that, like, a thing?

01:54.766 --> 01:56.725
Yeah. I do it every
couple months.

01:56.768 --> 01:59.206
Okay. Here you go.
And no, you can't film me.
I'm not signing a release.

01:59.249 --> 02:00.729
Well,
then it's your loss, then,

02:00.772 --> 02:02.992
because this doc's
coming together.

02:03.035 --> 02:06.430
-I'm thinking Oscar.
-Bad accident on the 101,

02:06.474 --> 02:09.216
VIP and wife,
chopper's five minutes out.

02:09.259 --> 02:10.956
Wait, VIP. What -- what VIP?

02:11.000 --> 02:14.308
Hey, Coppola. Let's go.
Jesse: Whoa, whoa, whoa.
You wanna go that way.

02:14.351 --> 02:17.441
[ Helicopter blades whirring ]

02:17.485 --> 02:20.183
Rorish: What do you got?!
Lost pulse en route.
Four minutes.

02:20.227 --> 02:22.229
Car crashed into
a construction truck.

02:22.272 --> 02:24.144
Post came through
the windshield.

02:24.187 --> 02:27.190
On my count. One, two, three!
Passenger -- Sonya Finn.
Altered. BP, 70 over 30.

02:27.234 --> 02:30.976
-Dislocated left hip.
-Rox, take over compressions!

02:31.020 --> 02:34.284
Holy crap! This is Drake Finn!
I got it!
I said Rox, Dr. Avila!

02:34.328 --> 02:36.199
You are not a character
in his movie.

02:36.243 --> 02:39.333
This is real life. Let's go.
Thready pulse. Cool extremities.
She's in shock.

02:39.376 --> 02:41.987
Come on. Let's go.

02:42.031 --> 02:44.468
We need to activate the massive
transfusion protocol.
Okay, let's go. Go, go.

02:44.512 --> 02:47.167
Already did that from dispatch.
Sonya, is there anyone
you want us to call?

02:47.210 --> 02:49.212
Oh, God. Why? Is he dead?

02:49.256 --> 02:50.213
No, no. We're working on him.

02:50.257 --> 02:52.259
Call my daughter, please.
Her name is Delia.

02:52.302 --> 02:54.348
Look out. Coming in.

02:54.391 --> 02:56.176
All right, guys, he's been down
six minutes.

02:56.219 --> 02:59.222
-We need an EPI and blood.
-Sonya: My phone's in my purse.

02:59.266 --> 03:02.138
Call Andrew Ferryman.
He needs to be here, too.

03:02.182 --> 03:04.314
-His agent? Seriously?
-Go make the call.

03:04.358 --> 03:07.056
Okay, left leg is shortened
and rotated internally.

03:07.099 --> 03:09.189
Okay, you got a dislocated hip,
and we're gonna have to

03:09.232 --> 03:11.365
put it back in, all right?
So I'm gonna give you some meds.
Drake!

03:11.408 --> 03:12.279
Somebody give me the bullet
on Mr. Finn.

03:12.322 --> 03:14.542
-Got a call from the board.
-Rox.

03:14.585 --> 03:16.370
This is the driver.
We've got a pipe that came

03:16.413 --> 03:18.372
through the windshield
and impaled him.

03:18.415 --> 03:20.635
Vitals are unstable.
Lost pulses en route.

03:20.678 --> 03:22.593
Page Dr. Leighton, tell him
to have an OR ready.

03:22.637 --> 03:24.291
I need an ultrasound
over here now.

03:24.334 --> 03:26.597
-What did the board have to say?
-"Don't let him die."

03:26.641 --> 03:28.773
Drake. Honey, talk to me.

03:28.817 --> 03:31.298
Okay, this is gonna be painful,
but it's gonna be fast.

03:31.341 --> 03:34.214
-Just do it.
-Three, two, one.

03:34.257 --> 03:35.476
[ Crunch ]
[ Screams ]

03:35.519 --> 03:37.434
-Okay, pulse is good.
-Get her off the board.

03:37.478 --> 03:39.523
-All right.
-Drake?

03:39.567 --> 03:41.090
Whoa, whoa, whoa,
whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.
Aah!

03:41.133 --> 03:42.613
Let me get some tape over here!
All right, we got
a fractured arm!

03:42.657 --> 03:44.746
Right away.
We'll splint it later.
All right?

03:44.789 --> 03:47.314
-Okay.
-Okay. Pulse. Back. Good job.

03:47.357 --> 03:48.532
-Ready?
-It's weak.

03:48.576 --> 03:50.360
-Are you ready to move him?
-Stop.

03:50.404 --> 03:52.580
Impalement is millimeters
from the aorta.

03:52.623 --> 03:55.800
It could sever any moment.
One wrong bump to the gurney,
and he is gone.

03:55.844 --> 03:57.585
Ready a surgical tray.

03:57.628 --> 04:00.544
I need betadine, a bovie,
and a suction over here, too.

04:00.588 --> 04:02.546
All right, he's going up.

04:02.590 --> 04:04.418
Your daughter is coming
from Santa Barbara,

04:04.461 --> 04:06.202
and I left a message
for the agent, all right?

04:06.246 --> 04:07.769
He's gotta know.
It's all over social media.

04:07.812 --> 04:10.337
You got time for social media,
you ain't doing your job.

04:10.380 --> 04:13.296
I can multitask.
Can we lose the studio audience?

04:13.340 --> 04:16.081
Guys, hey, please.
Clear the platform.

04:16.125 --> 04:18.170
Go. Thank you. Goodbye.

04:18.214 --> 04:20.521
We need something
to cut the metal
and remove it in pieces.

04:20.564 --> 04:22.479
Okay. I need a saw!
There's an angle grinder
on the fire truck.

04:22.523 --> 04:24.568
-I'm gonna go get it.
-Go.

04:24.612 --> 04:27.397
Rorish: Go, go, go.
All right, we've got incoming
ambulance bay.

04:27.441 --> 04:30.531
Diego, you take her to sides.
Jesse and I will take incoming.

04:30.574 --> 04:34.491
You'll have to fight
that crowd to get to them.

04:34.535 --> 04:36.276
[ Shouting indistinctly ]

04:36.319 --> 04:38.321
Man: [ Amplified voice ]
Please disperse.
We have a medical emergency.

04:38.365 --> 04:40.584
[ Crowd shouting ]
Clear the way.

04:40.628 --> 04:43.805
[ Siren wails ]

04:43.848 --> 04:46.547
♪♪

04:53.902 --> 04:55.425
-Clear it out! Clear it out!
-Okay, guys, guys, guys.

04:55.469 --> 04:57.253
Please, come on. Come on!
Bring it through!
Hey. Hey, buddy.

04:57.297 --> 04:59.429
[ Shouting continues ]

04:59.473 --> 05:04.608
[ Buzzing ]

05:04.652 --> 05:06.436
A few more millimeters!

05:06.480 --> 05:07.872
Andrew: No, I will not stay
back. I was told to be here.

05:07.916 --> 05:09.526
Dr. Avila left me a message.

05:09.570 --> 05:11.659
-Diego: Agent's here.
-Go get him.

05:11.702 --> 05:15.053
Hey.
Mr. Ferryman, this way.

05:15.097 --> 05:17.447
Rorish: Good job.
Campbell:
Little more, little more.

05:17.491 --> 05:19.144
Oh, my God.

05:19.188 --> 05:21.451
-Drake? Drake?
-Hey. Hey, hey, hey.

05:21.495 --> 05:24.019
-Got it.
-Hold it, hold it, hold it.

05:24.062 --> 05:25.499
-Ready?
-All right.

05:25.542 --> 05:27.370
Let's move this one out first.
Can I have laps?

05:27.414 --> 05:28.937
Okay, Drake.

05:28.980 --> 05:31.548
-Tie this up for me.
-Okay, go ahead. Ready.

05:31.592 --> 05:34.595
Campbell: Hold pressure
as soon as I pull this out.
There you go. Okay.

05:34.638 --> 05:36.510
Is -- is he gonna be okay?

05:36.553 --> 05:39.774
It's bad, but...
What do you mean it's bad?
What's happening?

05:39.817 --> 05:42.864
But his aorta's intact.
Sir, we have a private room
set up.

05:42.907 --> 05:44.300
Dr. Avila,
take him in now, please.

05:44.344 --> 05:45.606
No, I need to --
I need to be --

05:45.649 --> 05:47.216
Dr. Avila, take him there now.
Please.

05:47.259 --> 05:48.696
-But --
-Let's go. He's gonna be fine.

05:50.524 --> 05:54.615
BP is low, but it's holding.

05:54.658 --> 05:56.356
Is he gonna make it?

05:56.399 --> 05:59.271
Surgically, we've done
what we can. Time will tell.

05:59.315 --> 06:02.666
Hell of a job, Rox.

06:02.710 --> 06:04.842
[ Chuckles ]

06:04.886 --> 06:06.540
60-year-old female
fell down some stairs,

06:06.583 --> 06:08.498
landed on her head, actively
seizing for eight minutes.

06:08.542 --> 06:10.457
She's my mother.
Please help her.

06:10.500 --> 06:12.546
She get meds en route?
Pushed 6 of Ativan.
No response.

06:12.589 --> 06:15.679
All right, we got it from here.
Thank you.

06:15.723 --> 06:17.638
Center stage is full.
She's gotta go to sides.

06:17.681 --> 06:20.554
Right in here, guys.
Another 2
and load her with Dilantin?

06:20.597 --> 06:22.294
-Yeah.
-Ativan's in.

06:22.338 --> 06:25.297
Dilantin's coming out.
What's her medical history?

06:25.341 --> 06:28.431
Brain cancer four years ago,
but she's in remission now.

06:28.475 --> 06:31.565
Ever had seizures before?
No, just a few, after the --
after the cancer.

06:31.608 --> 06:33.044
She always managed them
with medication.

06:33.088 --> 06:34.655
Seizure broke.
All right, let's keep loading
the Dilantin.

06:34.698 --> 06:37.135
Let's get a CT scan.
We'll be right back.
You hang in there, okay?

06:37.179 --> 06:39.442
Come on. Coming through.

06:39.486 --> 06:41.401
Okay, so there was
"Deep Destruction."

06:41.444 --> 06:43.794
I saw that three times.
Oh. And "11.8."

06:43.838 --> 06:46.580
No one does a natural disaster
like Drake Finn.

06:46.623 --> 06:48.973
I really don't care.

06:49.017 --> 06:51.672
Come on. Drake Finn is
in the hospital.

06:51.715 --> 06:53.500
No way you don't care.

06:53.543 --> 06:56.503
There are, like, 50 different
ways I don't care.

06:56.546 --> 06:58.200
I'm trying to cheer you up.

06:58.243 --> 06:59.593
Why?

06:59.636 --> 07:02.987
Because your...boyfriend --
he...

07:03.031 --> 07:07.035
He died? Yes, Max died.
You can say it.

07:07.078 --> 07:10.473
I just wanna help.
Grieving is hard to do alone.

07:10.517 --> 07:15.347
[ Scoffs ] You sound
exactly like Leanne.

07:15.391 --> 07:19.221
Oh, my God. She sent you
to come talk to me, didn't she?

07:19.264 --> 07:22.659
-No, it's not like that.
-Then what is it like?

07:22.703 --> 07:25.619
[ Sighs ] Leanne told my dad
you could use a friend.

07:25.662 --> 07:27.708
So he asked me to come
hang out with you.

07:27.751 --> 07:31.973
Oh, is he paying you, too?
Come on. I mean, it does seem
like you could use a friend.

07:32.016 --> 07:36.456
I want to be sad.
I'm allowed to do that.

07:36.499 --> 07:41.025
Fine. Be sad.
I'm not leaving.

07:41.069 --> 07:43.637
[ Sighs ]

07:43.680 --> 07:46.509
How many different ways
can I say no?

07:46.553 --> 07:48.337
-How's the pain?
-You're not listening to me.

07:48.380 --> 07:50.731
I've given birth.
This isn't even close.

07:50.774 --> 07:53.603
Remember the bracelet you got.
I think I just paid that off.

07:53.647 --> 07:55.431
I'm not gonna talk about
his condition.

07:55.475 --> 07:57.651
No, that's not the kind of
publicity we're looking for.

07:57.694 --> 08:02.177
-No. No, that --
-How are you feeling?

08:02.220 --> 08:07.748
I'd cry, but Drake Finn
doesn't cry. He gets even.

08:07.791 --> 08:10.228
I saw that one.
Pretty sure that's in
all of them.

08:10.272 --> 08:13.275
Yes, I'm still here.
Okay, so you lost a lot
of blood on scene,

08:13.318 --> 08:15.582
but we've been transfusing you
since you arrived.

08:15.625 --> 08:19.020
I just need to look at your
wound here, check the sutures.

08:19.063 --> 08:21.718
Rox? What do you suggest?

08:21.762 --> 08:24.416
Uh, I don't know.

08:24.460 --> 08:27.985
We wanna prevent infection
post-surgery. Antibiotics.

08:28.029 --> 08:29.813
Yes.
Vanc and Zosyn, please.

08:29.857 --> 08:31.815
I wish Delia would
get here already.

08:31.859 --> 08:34.035
There will be no comment.
I'm hanging up now.
[ Cellphone beeps ]

08:34.078 --> 08:36.167
What's happening
with "Blood Donor"?
What?

08:36.211 --> 08:39.040
Oh, that's his next movie.
Denzel's supposed to direct it.

08:39.083 --> 08:42.086
I read the trades.

08:42.130 --> 08:44.219
We have a start date yet?
Stop. We're not talking
business now.

08:44.262 --> 08:46.830
[ Scoffs ]
It's a joke, right?

08:46.874 --> 08:48.092
[ Monitor beeping steadily ]

08:48.136 --> 08:51.139
[ Exhales shakily ]

08:51.182 --> 08:54.751
How's -- How's my mom?
CT scan is clear.
She's still in radiology.

08:54.795 --> 08:56.840
We're also getting an MRI.

08:56.884 --> 08:59.843
[ Indistinct conversations ]

08:59.887 --> 09:03.107
You, uh, do you think
the cancer could be back?

09:03.151 --> 09:06.458
[ Woman speaking indistinctly
over P.A. ]

09:06.502 --> 09:08.373
Dr. Willis?

09:08.417 --> 09:10.375
He's asking if the cancer
could be back.

09:10.419 --> 09:12.943
Oh, we don't know yet, but with
her history and the seizing,

09:12.987 --> 09:15.642
we just wanna rule it out.

09:15.685 --> 09:18.688
I should call the airline,
right?

09:18.732 --> 09:22.779
I, uh, I fly out
for Kenya tomorrow.

09:22.823 --> 09:24.651
Gonna teach for a year. It's
kind of a life-long dream,

09:24.694 --> 09:27.523
but now, I don't know. I just
feel like I should cancel.

09:27.567 --> 09:31.527
Wait for the MRI.
Should be back soon.

09:31.571 --> 09:33.660
[ Typing ]
[ Sighs ]

09:33.703 --> 09:35.836
Just, last time was rough.

09:37.838 --> 09:40.231
She couldn't sleep.

09:40.275 --> 09:42.799
Had to read to her for hours
just to relax her.

09:45.846 --> 09:47.674
[ Sighs ] I just gotta
keep it together.

09:47.717 --> 09:50.285
I can't, um, let her
see me worried, right?

09:51.765 --> 09:54.681
Don't worry till there's
something to worry about.

09:54.724 --> 09:59.642
We'll be back when we know
something, okay? Stay strong.

09:59.686 --> 10:01.818
Yeah.

10:01.862 --> 10:04.038
What's going on with you?

10:04.081 --> 10:06.214
Nothing.

10:06.257 --> 10:09.783
We've been to every
emergency room in the city.

10:09.826 --> 10:12.133
All the doctors say that
Dominic's fine, but he's not.

10:12.176 --> 10:15.963
It's just crying and sleeping.
That's what toddlers do.

10:16.006 --> 10:19.619
It comes out of nowhere.

10:19.662 --> 10:21.838
He gets really excited and then
he just falls asleep.

10:21.882 --> 10:23.710
I'm telling you,
something is wrong.

10:23.753 --> 10:26.060
I'll order blood tests
and a chest x-ray,

10:26.103 --> 10:29.324
and hopefully, the results
will tell us what's going on.

10:29.367 --> 10:31.326
[ Exhales sharply ] You're not
gonna find anything,

10:31.369 --> 10:33.981
just like the rest of them.

10:34.024 --> 10:35.765
You know what?

10:35.809 --> 10:37.549
Is Dr. Angus Leighton
still around?

10:37.593 --> 10:39.377
Uh-huh.

10:39.421 --> 10:41.379
Then I'd like to see him.

10:41.423 --> 10:42.859
[ Monitor beeping steadily ]

10:42.903 --> 10:45.732
Okay.

10:45.775 --> 10:47.429
[ Whispers ] I'll be back.

10:47.472 --> 10:50.780
Rox: You're being easier on me
than you are your residents.

10:50.824 --> 10:52.913
I'm not turning you
into a physician.

10:52.956 --> 10:54.828
There's a difference.

10:54.871 --> 10:56.656
But you know I can
handle it, right?

10:56.699 --> 10:58.092
You spend all day
with Willis.

10:58.135 --> 10:59.833
If you can handle him,
you can handle me.

10:59.876 --> 11:01.791
I don't know how well
I'm handling him.

11:01.835 --> 11:04.533
Relationships are difficult.

11:04.576 --> 11:07.884
-We're not in a relationship.
-Professional relationship.

11:07.928 --> 11:10.713
Yes.
Professional, definitely.

11:10.757 --> 11:12.280
Mm.

11:12.323 --> 11:14.935
He's pushing me away
for some reason.

11:14.978 --> 11:18.721
Maybe you're getting
too close.

11:18.765 --> 11:20.941
There's no other reason
to push someone away.

11:20.984 --> 11:23.378
At least, that's what
I always tell myself.

11:23.421 --> 11:25.032
Who are you pushing away?

11:25.075 --> 11:28.426
Oh, I'm not the pusher.
I'm the pushee.

11:28.470 --> 11:31.212
I was a terror at Ariel's age,
and I wasn't grieving.

11:31.255 --> 11:33.867
Mm.
Maybe she just, I don't know,
needs a little space.

11:33.910 --> 11:36.217
Well, I'm trying. But you
give 'em too much space,

11:36.260 --> 11:38.654
and they think you don't care.

11:38.698 --> 11:41.222
Thanks.

11:41.265 --> 11:42.876
-Hey.
-How'd it go?

11:42.919 --> 11:45.705
-I'm toast.
-Son, you don't know that.

11:45.748 --> 11:47.315
Yeah, you were there.
Detective Gomez was

11:47.358 --> 11:49.926
a decorated officer
whose widow moved everyone.

11:49.970 --> 11:52.407
And this judgment will go
on file with the medical board.

11:52.450 --> 11:53.930
No one
will ever hire me again.

11:53.974 --> 11:56.019
You're getting ahead
of yourself, Elliot.

11:56.063 --> 11:57.934
You have to wait
for the ruling. You can't --

11:57.978 --> 11:59.762
I'd rule against me.
Then it's a good thing
you don't decide the case.

11:59.806 --> 12:01.808
Yeah.

12:01.851 --> 12:02.809
I just wanna tell her
that I'm sorry.

12:02.852 --> 12:05.202
No, no, no, no, no.
No way, man. No can do.

12:05.246 --> 12:07.727
He's right. You can't admit
wrongdoing, son.

12:07.770 --> 12:10.860
Let the facts, not your
feelings, influence your case.

12:10.904 --> 12:14.255
Hi. I'm looking for Gladys
and Eugene Partridge.

12:14.298 --> 12:16.213
Gladys and Eugene Partridge?

12:16.257 --> 12:18.781
She means
Sonya and Drake Finn.

12:18.825 --> 12:22.089
Come on. You must be Delia.
They're right this way.

12:22.132 --> 12:25.527
-Hi, Madeline. How you doing?
-I'm okay.

12:25.570 --> 12:27.964
Helps that my doctor's
oppressively handsome.

12:28.008 --> 12:29.792
-[ Sighs ]
-And your nurse.

12:29.836 --> 12:32.142
[ Gasps ]

12:33.927 --> 12:37.104
I have the results
from your MRI.

12:37.147 --> 12:40.977
Cancer's back.

12:41.021 --> 12:42.849
I'm sorry.

12:42.892 --> 12:45.199
And the tumor's causing
a fluid build-up in your brain.

12:45.242 --> 12:48.115
-Damn it.
-You beat it before.

12:48.158 --> 12:50.421
By the skin of my teeth.

12:50.465 --> 12:53.424
[ Monitor beeping steadily ]

12:53.468 --> 12:56.776
-Results back?
-Great news, honey.

12:56.819 --> 12:59.909
-No cancer.
-[ Exhales deeply ]

12:59.953 --> 13:01.737
[ Madeline chuckles ]

13:04.218 --> 13:06.916
Oh, your mom's getting
a CAT scan.

13:06.960 --> 13:09.005
She should be back soon.
I tried to get here as fast
as I could,

13:09.049 --> 13:11.573
but it was so crazy outside.
I could barely get in.

13:11.616 --> 13:13.923
Okay, but you got here,
and you did great.

13:15.577 --> 13:24.499
♪♪

13:24.542 --> 13:27.110
-Can't believe you.
-It's -- it's not...

13:27.154 --> 13:29.634
No. Sorry.

13:29.678 --> 13:31.114
♪♪

13:31.158 --> 13:32.812
[ Sighs ]

13:32.855 --> 13:37.033
Okay, so tests were normal,
but there are more we can run.

13:37.077 --> 13:38.600
I'm really sorry if I was...

13:38.643 --> 13:40.645
You're a mom with a sick kid.
Nothing to be sorry about.

13:40.689 --> 13:43.300
-Angus: Hey, you paged me?
-Yeah, um, this is --

13:43.344 --> 13:46.129
I...don't know
if you remember me.

13:46.173 --> 13:49.176
Yvonne. Uh...
Of course I remember you.

13:49.219 --> 13:53.006
Um, hi.
Who is this little guy?

13:53.049 --> 13:55.138
-Dominic.
-Hi, Dominic.

13:55.182 --> 13:58.011
He's been sick. I was hoping
his father could help.

13:58.054 --> 14:00.317
-It's kind of my last resort.
-Yeah. When's he get here?

14:00.361 --> 14:01.928
He just did.

14:01.971 --> 14:03.930
♪♪

14:10.284 --> 14:11.720
It can't be easy to
discover that your dad's

14:11.763 --> 14:13.940
not who you thought.
Come on, I knew Drake was gay.

14:13.983 --> 14:16.943
Remarkable that you managed not
to say anything out loud.

14:16.986 --> 14:19.075
-I'm saying Delia had to know.
-Yeah.

14:19.119 --> 14:22.165
Even if she did know, he didn't
tell her. That's the point.

14:22.209 --> 14:23.688
So he lied. Everyone lies.

14:23.732 --> 14:25.865
I mean, that goes double
for D.C., triple for Hollywood.

14:25.908 --> 14:27.867
Well, on the rig,
we treat them and turf them.

14:27.910 --> 14:29.738
I don't know how you guys
deal with the drama.

14:29.781 --> 14:32.784
-I try to stay out of it.
-I film it.

14:32.828 --> 14:34.612
I need to talk to you.

14:34.656 --> 14:36.788
You can't deal with me, so you
pawn me off to someone else?

14:36.832 --> 14:39.226
Uh...can we talk about
this in private?

14:39.269 --> 14:40.880
Well, you already told
Dr. Campbell about it,

14:40.923 --> 14:42.359
so I guess
it's not private, then.

14:42.403 --> 14:45.362
Okay, I was trying to help you.
I didn't know what else to do.

14:45.406 --> 14:48.061
How about not asking
my friend to spy on me?

14:48.104 --> 14:50.846
I'm sorry.

14:50.890 --> 14:53.370
But you haven't spoken
to me in about a week.

14:53.414 --> 14:55.372
I'm not gonna start now.

14:55.416 --> 14:59.637
♪♪

14:59.681 --> 15:01.813
She doesn't want her son
to know the cancer's back.

15:01.857 --> 15:03.903
-She can't do that.
-Sure, she can.

15:03.946 --> 15:05.426
It's her call to make.

15:05.469 --> 15:06.688
Says the man who didn't want
his brother to know

15:06.731 --> 15:09.082
that he had CHF.
-It's different.

15:09.125 --> 15:12.433
Jose was the one who was sick,
and I was in denial.

15:12.476 --> 15:15.958
-Madeline's not.
-She's hurting her son.

15:16.002 --> 15:18.265
Or helping him.
You can't help somebody
by lying.

15:18.308 --> 15:21.137
Sometimes you can. Hey.

15:21.181 --> 15:23.139
Is that so?

15:23.183 --> 15:26.273
You ever wonder why they call
the good lies, white lies?

15:26.316 --> 15:29.189
Just saying.

15:29.232 --> 15:30.799
Was that aimed at me?

15:30.842 --> 15:32.235
Sometimes the lie is
a good thing?

15:32.279 --> 15:36.022
Look, my father may not like it,
and it is no fun to hear,

15:36.065 --> 15:38.502
but we needed to know what
really happened to my brother.

15:38.546 --> 15:42.506
So spare me the yoga wisdom
and namaste-out of it.

15:42.550 --> 15:43.333
Ethan, I wasn't talking
about you.

15:43.377 --> 15:45.509
I was just making conversation.

15:45.553 --> 15:48.034
Nothing's wrong, huh?

15:48.077 --> 15:51.037
-No, nothing's wrong.
-Mm.

15:51.080 --> 15:55.519
I'm sorry.
I didn't call you before.

15:55.563 --> 16:00.176
You know, I'm gonna check him
out as -- as a doctor. I should.

16:00.220 --> 16:01.961
Um... [ Clears throat ]

16:02.004 --> 16:04.006
You say he falls asleep
suddenly?

16:04.050 --> 16:06.966
Yeah, a few times a day,
usually after he's crying

16:07.009 --> 16:09.359
or gets upset and then he just,
he wakes right back up.

16:09.403 --> 16:12.275
Fever or rashes? Ah.

16:12.319 --> 16:13.842
-Ah.
-No.

16:13.885 --> 16:17.454
[ Monitor beeping steadily ]

16:17.498 --> 16:22.938
♪♪

16:22.982 --> 16:26.898
So...why didn't you call me?

16:26.942 --> 16:30.598
It was one night, Angus.

16:30.641 --> 16:33.166
I thought I could handle it
on my own.

16:33.209 --> 16:35.255
When Dominic got sick,
none of the other doctors

16:35.298 --> 16:37.474
would believe me that there's
anything wrong with him.

16:37.518 --> 16:39.172
Well, I believe you.

16:39.215 --> 16:42.175
And I'm gonna take care
of Dominic.

16:42.218 --> 16:43.437
[ Crying ]

16:43.480 --> 16:45.352
I promise.

16:45.395 --> 16:49.269
Thank you. [ Sniffles ]

16:49.312 --> 16:54.752
♪♪

16:54.796 --> 16:56.189
What's your full name?

16:56.232 --> 16:57.451
Madeline Mandel.

16:57.494 --> 16:59.670
Mm-hmm.
And what year are we in?

16:59.714 --> 17:01.020
2018.

17:01.063 --> 17:02.673
And where are right now?

17:02.717 --> 17:04.893
Uh, Pamplona.
Running with the bulls.

17:04.936 --> 17:07.504
-Where's your red scarf?
-[ Chuckles ]

17:07.548 --> 17:10.594
I ask these questions
to everyone who's
suffered a head injury.

17:10.638 --> 17:14.337
I'm at Angels. Practically lived
here four years ago.

17:14.381 --> 17:16.035
You think I wouldn't
remember it?

17:16.078 --> 17:19.473
I also remember my home,
where I'd much rather be.

17:19.516 --> 17:21.257
Mom, they're just being
thorough.

17:21.301 --> 17:23.607
[ Sighs ] Did I pass the test?

17:23.651 --> 17:26.306
With flying colors.
We'll be back.

17:26.349 --> 17:28.308
[ Monitor beeping steadily ]

17:28.351 --> 17:32.094
What's going on?
Dr. Willis has concerns
about Madeline's competence.

17:32.138 --> 17:34.227
What?
She has
a traumatic brain injury.

17:34.270 --> 17:37.143
Nice try. She can make
her own medical decisions.

17:37.186 --> 17:39.188
She's lying to her son
about the cancer.

17:39.232 --> 17:41.799
As long as she's of sound mind,
that is her call to make.

17:41.843 --> 17:43.105
But Jake would want to
be there for her.

17:43.149 --> 17:45.107
Well...
He'd want to help her,
and she's gonna need it.

17:45.151 --> 17:48.893
She's not thinking rationally.
Oh, no. She is.
Not sure about you.

17:48.937 --> 17:51.896
Willis, HIPAA protects
her privacy.

17:51.940 --> 17:53.202
She decides who she tells.

17:53.246 --> 17:55.813
She decides how she lives
or how she dies.

17:55.857 --> 17:58.381
And no doctor can take
that away, and they won't,

17:58.425 --> 18:00.862
not on my watch.

18:08.435 --> 18:09.740
Hey.

18:09.784 --> 18:13.701
I don't care that he's gay.
I've heard the rumors.

18:13.744 --> 18:18.358
But my mom...

18:18.401 --> 18:20.273
it's gonna break her heart.

18:20.316 --> 18:24.146
My father wasn't a superstar.
He was barely employed,

18:24.190 --> 18:27.280
but I caught him
cheating on my mom.

18:27.323 --> 18:29.456
I was
a little younger than you.

18:29.499 --> 18:33.895
He made me keep it a secret,
and it tore me up.

18:33.938 --> 18:35.940
You never told her?

18:35.984 --> 18:37.290
Well, I didn't have to.

18:37.333 --> 18:40.075
I caught her with
someone else, so...

18:40.119 --> 18:42.208
No point after that.

18:42.251 --> 18:45.515
You do have a point, though,
right?

18:45.559 --> 18:49.171
Your parents' marriage
isn't your responsibility.

18:49.215 --> 18:51.434
You can't take
that burden on.

18:51.478 --> 18:54.220
Delia?

18:54.263 --> 18:55.264
Do I tell her or not?

18:57.048 --> 18:59.442
Hi, Mom. You okay?

18:59.486 --> 19:01.227
I'm tougher than I look.

19:03.490 --> 19:06.014
Your dad told me
what you saw.

19:06.057 --> 19:08.495
It's not what you think.

19:14.501 --> 19:15.763
He's gay.

19:15.806 --> 19:18.374
I know.

19:18.418 --> 19:20.333
What?

19:20.376 --> 19:22.378
I think we should give them
some privacy.

19:22.422 --> 19:24.119
I don't know if I should
leave my patient alone.

19:24.163 --> 19:26.165
Don't leave me with her.

19:26.208 --> 19:27.818
You were only 8.

19:27.862 --> 19:30.430
He met Andrew
and fell in love.

19:30.473 --> 19:33.302
He'd been lying to himself
for so long and then to me.

19:33.346 --> 19:35.870
He didn't wanna lie anymore.

19:35.913 --> 19:38.351
But he did.

19:38.394 --> 19:42.964
He kept lying to me,
and then you did it, too.

19:43.007 --> 19:45.184
-Dr. Avila, we should...
-What kind of a mother

19:45.227 --> 19:47.925
lies to her daughter
for half her life?

19:47.969 --> 19:50.885
Get her away from me.

19:50.928 --> 19:53.670
Get her away from me
before I scream.

19:53.714 --> 19:54.758
-Delia, please.
-[ Crying ]

19:54.802 --> 19:57.718
[ Whispers ] Just go.

19:57.761 --> 19:59.763
Delia...

19:59.807 --> 20:02.940
[ Sobbing ]

20:02.984 --> 20:04.203
All right,
ultrasound looks good.

20:04.246 --> 20:06.335
Yeah,
everything looks good.

20:06.379 --> 20:08.816
Kid's fine.
She's scamming you.

20:08.859 --> 20:10.339
We are not discussing this
right now.

20:10.383 --> 20:11.819
You need to take
a paternity test.

20:11.862 --> 20:13.429
Dominic? Dom!
What did I just say?

20:13.473 --> 20:14.865
Help! He's not breathing. Angus!

20:16.650 --> 20:19.957
What's the matter,
little buddy? Big breath.

20:20.001 --> 20:22.177
[ Exhales deeply ]

20:22.221 --> 20:24.092
-He's breathing just fine.
-One more.

20:24.135 --> 20:26.747
He wasn't a second ago.
Why does this keep happening?

20:26.790 --> 20:31.491
-There. Did you see that?
-No.

20:31.534 --> 20:34.015
-What are you doing?
-Checking his monitor history.

20:34.058 --> 20:37.061
[ Typing ]

20:38.541 --> 20:40.239
There.
There it is. V-tach.

20:40.282 --> 20:42.545
It's only six beats,
but it is there,

20:42.589 --> 20:43.981
right when she said
he stopped breathing.
Kids are squirmy, okay?

20:44.025 --> 20:47.811
Could be ectopy, could be...
motion artifact.

20:47.855 --> 20:50.553
-He's got a growing heart.
-Or maybe we missed something.

20:50.597 --> 20:52.163
I think we need to get
a stress test.

20:52.207 --> 20:54.688
-Dude.
-Are you gonna help me or not?

20:57.168 --> 20:59.170
-We made the wrong choice.
-No, no, no. We did what

20:59.214 --> 21:01.085
we thought was best
for Delia at the time.

21:01.129 --> 21:03.087
No, we did what youthought was
best for youat the time.

21:03.131 --> 21:05.960
Guys, please, stop.
It's not the time --
Andrew, shut the hell up.

21:06.003 --> 21:09.006
Okay, excuse me. We need to...
I just destroyed
the most important person

21:09.050 --> 21:10.791
in the world to me.
-Please.

21:10.834 --> 21:12.445
We need to talk about
his condition.

21:14.621 --> 21:17.972
You've developed Disseminated
Intravascular Coagulation.

21:18.015 --> 21:21.671
It affects your ability
to clot.

21:21.715 --> 21:23.804
Your body is starting
to shut down.

21:23.847 --> 21:25.849
[ Monitor beeping steadily ]

21:25.893 --> 21:27.808
So...what are you gonna do?

21:27.851 --> 21:29.288
Everything we possibly can.

21:30.854 --> 21:33.161
But our options are limited.

21:33.204 --> 21:36.295
There's nothing you can do,
is there?

21:36.338 --> 21:39.254
Mr. Finn,
we never give up here.

21:39.298 --> 21:49.308
♪♪

21:49.351 --> 21:54.095
♪♪

21:54.138 --> 21:56.184
[ Door closes ]

21:56.227 --> 22:02.277
♪♪

22:02.321 --> 22:04.540
What in God's name
is wrong with you?

22:04.584 --> 22:06.020
I'm telling a story
about this place,

22:06.063 --> 22:07.021
the good and the bad.

22:07.064 --> 22:08.501
And invading
a patient's privacy?

22:08.544 --> 22:12.069
Drake's a fraud.
We provide our patients
with medical care here.

22:12.113 --> 22:15.551
-We don't judge them.
-We judge 'em all the time.

22:15.595 --> 22:17.336
Go home.

22:17.379 --> 22:18.641
What?

22:18.685 --> 22:21.209
You've been here for months
already, and we've all tried

22:21.252 --> 22:23.603
to teach you, but you are
not getting it.

22:23.646 --> 22:24.952
Getting what?
My movie's the truth.

22:24.995 --> 22:28.651
Your truth lacks humanity
and compassion.

22:28.695 --> 22:30.479
And sadly,
I fear, you do, too.

22:32.133 --> 22:34.875
Now get out of my sight.

22:34.918 --> 22:38.357
♪♪

22:52.327 --> 22:53.546
[ Water splashing ]

22:53.589 --> 22:55.417
Dr. Willis?

22:55.461 --> 22:59.595
Listen, I-I just can't thank
you enough for helping my mom,

22:59.639 --> 23:01.162
for, you know,
making her better.

23:01.205 --> 23:02.598
Oh, she's tough.
[ Drying hands ]

23:02.642 --> 23:04.426
She did most
of the work herself.

23:04.470 --> 23:07.690
Well, then, thank you
for helping me.

23:07.734 --> 23:09.518
I was panicking
for no reason.

23:09.562 --> 23:12.913
I'm just so glad
she's gonna be okay.

23:12.956 --> 23:14.349
Thanks again, Doc.

23:16.569 --> 23:18.222
Anytime.

23:26.274 --> 23:29.712
[ Exhales slowly ]

23:29.756 --> 23:32.280
I'm supposed to be taking
a test right now.

23:32.323 --> 23:33.455
What class?

23:35.501 --> 23:38.808
Psychology. [ Chuckles ]

23:38.852 --> 23:43.465
Delia,
your father's very sick.

23:43.509 --> 23:45.162
I know.

23:45.206 --> 23:47.774
No, honey, he's sicker
than you know.

23:47.817 --> 23:49.384
What are you talking about?

23:49.428 --> 23:52.866
You need to go see him.

23:52.909 --> 23:56.522
No, screw him. Screw Andrew.
Screw my mom.

24:02.832 --> 24:06.401
I don't know what to do.

24:06.445 --> 24:09.056
Yeah, you do.

24:09.099 --> 24:11.101
Or you wouldn't still
be here.

24:14.496 --> 24:16.063
Hey.

24:16.106 --> 24:17.064
[ Indistinct conversations ]

24:17.107 --> 24:19.066
How's Ariel?

24:19.109 --> 24:21.721
I think I screwed up.

24:21.764 --> 24:23.679
Not the first time.
Won't be the last.

24:23.723 --> 24:25.899
[ Imitating Jesse ] "Oh, no.
You didn't screw up, Leanne.

24:25.942 --> 24:28.075
You were just doing
what you thought was right."

24:28.118 --> 24:29.859
That really what
you want to hear?

24:29.903 --> 24:33.210
No. What I wanna hear

24:33.254 --> 24:35.212
is that the courts are
granting me custody of Ariel.

24:35.256 --> 24:38.128
Nobody knows better than you
that there are things outside

24:38.172 --> 24:39.216
of your control.

24:39.260 --> 24:41.349
And sometimes
those things turn bad.

24:41.392 --> 24:43.786
You and Ariel have that
in common.

24:43.830 --> 24:45.527
Yeah.
She learned it too young.

24:45.571 --> 24:48.095
She doesn't expect things
to go her way.

24:48.138 --> 24:50.489
Worse.
She's sure they won't.

24:53.317 --> 24:54.623
-Ooh.
-Feel that?

24:54.667 --> 24:55.798
Yeah.

24:55.842 --> 24:59.062
[ Indistinct conversations ]

24:59.106 --> 25:00.281
Jake leave?

25:00.324 --> 25:02.805
He went to pack.
He'll be back.

25:02.849 --> 25:05.547
You really not
gonna tell him?

25:05.591 --> 25:10.813
If he knew I was sick again,
cancel his trip.

25:10.857 --> 25:16.036
Be just like last time.
Jake put his life on hold.

25:16.079 --> 25:17.341
[ Scoffs ]
Destroyed his marriage.

25:17.385 --> 25:20.040
Letting him do that again
would be selfish.

25:20.083 --> 25:21.607
There are some people
that would say that

25:21.650 --> 25:23.043
not letting him be
with his mother

25:23.086 --> 25:24.566
when she might die
is selfish.

25:24.610 --> 25:27.743
Some people.

25:27.787 --> 25:29.963
Do you get this involved
with all your patients?

25:30.006 --> 25:32.792
-No.
-So what is it about me exactly?

25:32.835 --> 25:36.622
When my mother was
on her death bed,

25:36.665 --> 25:39.799
my father sent my brother
to summer camp.

25:39.842 --> 25:42.236
And she was gone
by the time he got home.

25:42.279 --> 25:44.630
He never
got to say goodbye.

25:44.673 --> 25:49.025
And it ate at him
his whole life.

25:49.069 --> 25:52.333
And I'll never forgive my father
for doing that to him.

25:52.376 --> 25:56.380
I gave Jake life
31 years ago.

25:56.424 --> 26:00.776
I'm giving him life
again today.

26:00.820 --> 26:03.083
That's my job as a parent.

26:03.126 --> 26:06.042
♪♪

26:06.086 --> 26:10.612
[ Door opens ]

26:10.656 --> 26:12.048
[ Clears throat ]

26:12.092 --> 26:14.181
Why'd you throw me
under the bus?

26:14.224 --> 26:18.446
You told Ariel we sent you
to talk to her.

26:18.489 --> 26:20.622
Because it's what you did?

26:20.666 --> 26:23.190
No, I asked you
to help her out,

26:23.233 --> 26:26.846
not embarrass her.
-Because she's my friend, right?

26:26.889 --> 26:29.805
Well, isn't telling the truth
part of being a friend?

26:29.849 --> 26:32.765
Not always.
Really? Because you've been
pretty big on honesty before,

26:32.808 --> 26:34.984
unless you think
lying's okay now.

26:35.028 --> 26:36.769
Emily, I...
Or maybe you're saying that
being a friend

26:36.812 --> 26:39.510
means being dishonest, which is
a whole other bag of crazy.

26:39.554 --> 26:41.425
Okay, okay, okay. Enough.

26:41.469 --> 26:42.688
All right?

26:42.731 --> 26:44.167
You win.

26:44.211 --> 26:46.692
-Uh, I do?
-You're a good person.

26:48.781 --> 26:50.783
Can I take a little
credit for that?

26:50.826 --> 26:53.786
Yes, Dad. You can take
all the credit.

26:58.486 --> 27:00.793
Hey.

27:00.836 --> 27:01.924
What are you doing
out of bed?

27:01.968 --> 27:03.970
I had to get out
of that room.

27:04.013 --> 27:06.102
We can move you
to another room.

27:06.146 --> 27:08.061
[ Sighs ]
I stayed married to a man

27:08.104 --> 27:11.630
who was in love
with another man.

27:11.673 --> 27:13.370
[ Whispers ]
What's wrong with me?

27:15.546 --> 27:17.548
I'm not qualified to comment.

27:18.941 --> 27:21.596
I've been living a lie.

27:21.640 --> 27:24.338
And worse, I've made
my daughter live a lie.

27:26.035 --> 27:28.603
[ Sighs ] You have kids?

27:28.647 --> 27:30.170
One.

27:30.213 --> 27:32.476
Bet you're good at it.

27:32.520 --> 27:35.349
Nobody's good at it.

27:35.392 --> 27:37.656
We just do the best we can.

27:37.699 --> 27:40.093
It's just so hard.
You want them to look up to you

27:40.136 --> 27:43.574
and think you got it
all together.

27:43.618 --> 27:46.839
-Mm-hmm.
-You just want 'em to feel safe.

27:46.882 --> 27:48.797
Someone I admire
once said to me,

27:48.841 --> 27:52.845
our only job is to love them

27:52.888 --> 27:55.674
and to make sure
they know it every day.

27:55.717 --> 28:02.768
♪♪

28:04.160 --> 28:05.988
I know it seems like
baby boot camp,

28:06.032 --> 28:08.208
but we're looking for changes
in his heart rhythm

28:08.251 --> 28:12.255
based on stress.
-Angus, I trust you.

28:14.867 --> 28:17.043
I didn't...

28:17.086 --> 28:19.785
I didn't do it on purpose.

28:19.828 --> 28:22.135
[ Sniffles ]
Yvonne,
I would never suggest...

28:22.178 --> 28:25.878
But...I don't regret it.

28:25.921 --> 28:28.750
Not for a minute.

28:30.796 --> 28:32.493
He wakes me up every morning

28:32.536 --> 28:35.409
with this delicious,
giant smile on his face.

28:35.452 --> 28:38.673
He loves me so completely.

28:38.717 --> 28:41.807
Dom's the best thing
ever happened to me.

28:43.243 --> 28:44.810
[ Monitor beeping ]

28:44.853 --> 28:46.246
There it is.

28:46.289 --> 28:47.638
CPVT.

28:47.682 --> 28:48.814
Is that bad?

28:48.857 --> 28:50.380
It's a genetic condition.

28:50.424 --> 28:51.730
But the important thing is

28:51.773 --> 28:53.470
that we caught it early,
thanks to you.

28:53.514 --> 28:55.603
So is he gonna be okay?

28:55.646 --> 28:57.083
Dominic will need
life-long medication,

28:57.126 --> 29:00.347
and we'll need to implant
a defibrillator.

29:02.218 --> 29:06.396
Hey. Hey, he's gonna be okay.
All right?

29:06.440 --> 29:09.835
-Oh.
-[ Exhales deeply ]

29:13.099 --> 29:14.840
Can I get you anything?

29:14.883 --> 29:17.451
Oh, you're very sweet,
but no.

29:21.411 --> 29:24.980
-You understand why I'm --
-No, no, I don't need to.

29:25.024 --> 29:27.809
Personally, I admire
what you're doing.

29:27.853 --> 29:29.811
Oh.

29:29.855 --> 29:32.422
[ Monitor beeping erratically ]
Madeline?

29:32.466 --> 29:35.338
Mad-- Dr. Willis! Dr. Willis!

29:35.382 --> 29:38.037
Okay. Come on, guys. Let's go.

29:42.955 --> 29:45.914
Have you seen Delia?

29:45.958 --> 29:49.004
[ Sighs ]
Just tell me, is she okay?

29:49.048 --> 29:50.005
I don't know.

29:50.049 --> 29:54.880
There's no such thing as
a gay action hero.

29:54.923 --> 29:57.665
What was I supposed to do?
Tell the truth?
Yes.

29:57.708 --> 29:59.406
Hey, do you know who
you're talking to?

29:59.449 --> 30:02.713
No. I wanna hear what
she has to say.

30:04.237 --> 30:08.067
Go ahead. Say it.

30:08.110 --> 30:11.157
Forget that I'm Drake Finn.
I want the truth.

30:13.289 --> 30:16.249
Delia woke up this morning
with a family,

30:16.292 --> 30:18.817
only to find out that
you three are a family,

30:18.860 --> 30:21.907
and she's on the outside,
looking in.

30:21.950 --> 30:24.387
[ Sighs ]

30:28.696 --> 30:30.045
You're right.

30:30.089 --> 30:33.005
She's right.

30:33.048 --> 30:35.877
I wanted to have it all.

30:35.921 --> 30:37.923
But the truth is, I'd give it
all back right now

30:37.966 --> 30:39.576
to make this better.

30:42.057 --> 30:44.930
All of it?

30:44.973 --> 30:50.152
[ Sighs ] Maybe I'd keep
the house in Maui.

30:50.196 --> 30:51.023
-[ Exhales deeply ]
-[ Chuckles ]

30:51.066 --> 30:52.981
Will you come here, please?

30:53.025 --> 31:01.381
♪♪

31:01.424 --> 31:05.341
Listen, I don't know
what I can do

31:05.385 --> 31:07.169
to make this up to you.

31:07.213 --> 31:12.087
But I will spend every single
day just thinking of ways.

31:12.131 --> 31:14.960
Are you really my father?

31:15.003 --> 31:17.136
Oh, don't.

31:17.179 --> 31:19.094
Well, how would I know?

31:19.138 --> 31:21.140
Oh...

31:21.183 --> 31:22.489
'Cause you look like me?

31:22.532 --> 31:24.534
I look like Mom.

31:24.578 --> 31:26.058
Ah, but the beautiful smile.
[ Chuckles ]

31:26.101 --> 31:29.496
That's all me.

31:29.539 --> 31:31.367
You're such a narcissist.

31:31.411 --> 31:34.022
But a charming one.
[ Chuckles ]

31:34.066 --> 31:36.024
-Come here.
-I love you.

31:36.068 --> 31:38.200
Oh.

31:38.244 --> 31:39.723
[ Monitor beeping erratically ]

31:39.767 --> 31:41.116
Dad?

31:41.160 --> 31:42.683
-Drake? Drake?
-Do something.

31:42.726 --> 31:44.598
-Hold on, hold on.
-Drake? What's happening? Drake!

31:44.641 --> 31:47.949
-Oh!
-I need some help in here!

31:55.130 --> 31:56.958
Mom!
Dr. Willis, what happened?

31:57.002 --> 32:00.179
She just started seizing again.
Why? You said
that she was fine.

32:00.222 --> 32:02.181
I did not say she was fine.

32:02.224 --> 32:04.226
For her, it's important
to stay calm.

32:04.270 --> 32:06.663
-Jesse, we have to paralyze her.
-Wait. What?

32:06.707 --> 32:08.752
-Okay.
-Incoming!
--Rox, what happened?

32:08.796 --> 32:11.233
He lost consciousness
and started vomiting blood.

32:11.277 --> 32:12.626
I got him here as fast
as I could.

32:12.669 --> 32:13.975
Okay, we've already maxed out
his dopamine.

32:14.019 --> 32:15.411
Let's start him
on a Levophed drip.

32:15.455 --> 32:19.111
Okay, Jesse. Hey, she is not
gonna die tonight.

32:19.154 --> 32:21.591
-Go set up an EVD.
-She maxed out on Dilantin?

32:21.635 --> 32:23.680
How much steroids
did she take?

32:23.724 --> 32:26.466
The anti-seizure meds didn't
work, and the steroids failed.

32:26.509 --> 32:31.123
What the hell are you doing?
Is -- is her cancer back?

32:32.733 --> 32:34.996
They're inserting
the intercranial drain

32:35.040 --> 32:36.606
to remove excess fluid.

32:36.650 --> 32:39.566
Wait, what -- what...Wait, wait,
I-I don't understand. It...

32:39.609 --> 32:41.611
-The Levophed isn't working.
-It takes time.

32:41.655 --> 32:44.136
-What else can we do?
-Uh...

32:44.179 --> 32:46.268
Okay, get me
2 units of PRBCs.

32:46.312 --> 32:48.879
Risa, I need more FFPs
and platelets.

32:48.923 --> 32:50.185
[ Sputtering ]

32:50.229 --> 32:51.447
He is not protecting
his airways.

32:51.491 --> 32:53.101
Give me 120 sux
and 20 etomidate.

32:53.145 --> 32:55.103
Rox, you intubate.

32:55.147 --> 32:58.454
-Answer me. Is her cancer back?
-Jake, listen to me.

32:58.498 --> 33:01.022
Your mom was having refractory
seizures from the fall --

33:01.066 --> 33:04.243
common in severe concussions.
-Dr. Willis, is that true?

33:04.286 --> 33:06.071
This drain's gonna relieve
the pressure...
[ Whirring ]

33:06.114 --> 33:09.117
...but you need to know
that she --
Dr. Willis.

33:09.161 --> 33:12.338
♪♪

33:12.381 --> 33:15.254
-It's working.
-Good.

33:15.297 --> 33:16.995
All right, she's gonna need a CT
to confirm the placement.

33:17.038 --> 33:19.345
-Let's get her up there.
-Let's bring her up, Jesse.

33:19.388 --> 33:22.174
Here we go. Come on, guys.
Let's move her out. Let's go.

33:22.217 --> 33:26.482
-What now?
-BP is holding. Now we wait.

33:26.526 --> 33:29.746
Dr. Willis, as of right now,

33:29.790 --> 33:31.748
Madeline Mandel is
no longer your patient.

33:31.792 --> 33:33.402
Wait a minute.
I don't work for you.

33:33.446 --> 33:35.970
No, for me? No, no, you don't.
But you do work in this ER,

33:36.014 --> 33:38.103
and I run this ER.

33:38.146 --> 33:41.367
So I get to decide who sees
what patients.

33:41.410 --> 33:45.240
You are no longer
in charge of her care.

33:45.284 --> 33:47.721
♪♪

33:47.764 --> 33:50.028
Excuse me.

33:50.071 --> 33:53.379
They gave him
the internal defibrillator.

33:53.422 --> 33:57.165
He's gonna be all right.
Good. Now you can deal
with the paternity issues.

33:57.209 --> 33:58.384
I am dealing with them.

33:58.427 --> 34:01.213
You're a doctor.
She's a stripper.

34:01.256 --> 34:04.651
Yeah. It took me a minute,

34:04.694 --> 34:06.957
but I remember
when she hit on you.

34:07.001 --> 34:08.959
And every detail
of that night

34:09.003 --> 34:11.179
since you told me
again and again --
Okay, okay.

34:11.223 --> 34:13.138
[ Whispers ] Would you keep
your voice down, please?

34:13.181 --> 34:15.357
[ Sighs ] She wants money.

34:15.401 --> 34:16.793
I don't make any money.

34:16.837 --> 34:18.230
-You're the perfect mark.
-Why? 'Cause I'm stupid?

34:18.273 --> 34:21.842
No, 'cause you're too damn
nice and trusting.

34:24.366 --> 34:28.109
Here's the thing.
I'm not ready to be a dad.

34:30.285 --> 34:34.376
Having a kid right now would
blow up my entire life,

34:34.420 --> 34:37.292
but if Dominic is...

34:37.336 --> 34:40.382
my son...

34:40.426 --> 34:44.473
then I will do
the right thing.

34:44.517 --> 34:47.346
[ Inhales deeply ]

34:51.350 --> 34:55.093
-You are looking much better.
-I'm a fighter.

34:55.136 --> 34:56.746
So am I.

34:56.790 --> 34:58.313
Thank you for not giving up.

34:58.357 --> 35:01.360
I told you,
we never give up here.

35:03.362 --> 35:07.148
So how much longer do we
have to watch this?

35:07.192 --> 35:09.716
Can't disappoint
the adoring fans.

35:09.759 --> 35:12.240
You're alive.
Isn't that enough?

35:12.284 --> 35:13.676
They can ever get enough.

35:13.720 --> 35:17.941
Neither can he.

35:17.985 --> 35:23.077
♪♪

35:23.121 --> 35:26.167
Delia...

35:26.211 --> 35:28.082
I love you.

35:28.126 --> 35:30.563
I love you, too, Mom.

35:32.956 --> 35:35.394
But I'm still mad.

35:35.437 --> 35:42.575
♪♪

35:42.618 --> 35:46.405
The house in Maui would make
a nice apology gift.

35:46.448 --> 35:52.498
♪♪

35:52.541 --> 35:55.153
[ Siren wailing ]

35:55.196 --> 35:57.155
[ Sighs ]

36:00.158 --> 36:01.898
Why are you acting
like this?

36:04.162 --> 36:06.251
I'm just trying to be
your friend.

36:06.294 --> 36:09.341
-You're in pain and I care --
-I'm not in pain.

36:09.384 --> 36:14.259
And nobody asked you to care.

36:14.302 --> 36:17.000
Okay.

36:17.044 --> 36:18.698
You know what?

36:18.741 --> 36:21.222
You can try and fix your life
through your patients,

36:21.266 --> 36:24.443
you can push me away,
you can push everyone away,

36:24.486 --> 36:26.445
then the only one you'll have
left to torture is you.

36:26.488 --> 36:29.099
Have fun.

36:29.143 --> 36:31.319
I don't know who you think
you are, but you're not my wife.

36:33.539 --> 36:35.976
You're not my girlfriend.
You're not my shrink.

36:36.019 --> 36:39.936
No. I'm just a person
riding on the rig with you...

36:39.980 --> 36:43.375
until today,
'cause now...I'm done.

36:43.418 --> 36:49.555
♪♪

36:49.598 --> 36:51.992
You 9-1-1 paged us
to the break room?

36:52.035 --> 36:54.255
You know, you're not even
supposed to be here.

36:54.299 --> 36:56.475
You wanna tell me
what was so important?

36:56.518 --> 36:58.694
What...what's going on?

37:01.393 --> 37:03.308
I wanted to see you.

37:03.351 --> 37:08.400
♪♪

37:08.443 --> 37:12.230
They told me that I shouldn't
apologize, but I am so sorry.

37:12.273 --> 37:14.319
I mean, I just -- I wish that
I could go back and --

37:14.362 --> 37:16.625
I'm dropping the case.

37:19.280 --> 37:22.631
-You what?
-Javi was so stubborn.

37:22.675 --> 37:24.981
If he refused
to do something,

37:25.025 --> 37:27.810
it was impossible
to change his mind.

37:27.854 --> 37:29.682
I saw how you tried
to help him.

37:29.725 --> 37:32.554
I also saw how hard
you took it when he died.

37:32.598 --> 37:36.645
How? How could you see that?

37:36.689 --> 37:39.213
He showed me.

37:39.257 --> 37:44.392
♪♪

37:44.436 --> 37:46.612
I can't get Javi back.

37:46.655 --> 37:49.441
I just needed to know that
someone tried their best

37:49.484 --> 37:53.140
to save him.

37:53.183 --> 37:54.620
And you did.

37:56.796 --> 37:59.755
Take care of yourself.

37:59.799 --> 38:02.454
♪♪

38:02.497 --> 38:05.587
-[ Sighs ]
-What did you show her?

38:05.631 --> 38:08.938
♪♪

38:08.982 --> 38:11.593
...get you up
to radiology now.

38:11.637 --> 38:14.683
I'm not going anywhere until
that little girl's okay.

38:14.727 --> 38:18.644
Take me to the OR. I have to get a CT of your head, okay? I need to.

38:18.687 --> 38:20.733
This isn't a discussion. You got me?

38:20.776 --> 38:22.517
I'll be damned.

38:22.561 --> 38:25.346
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
Hey, we need Ativan now. Now!

38:25.390 --> 38:27.566
What's happening? He's seizing.
What does it look like?

38:27.609 --> 38:31.613
-I didn't even know I had it.
-Diego...

38:31.657 --> 38:37.271
♪♪

38:37.315 --> 38:38.577
I just wanna tell her
that I'm sorry.

38:38.620 --> 38:41.493
No, no, no, no, no.
No way, man. No can do.

38:41.536 --> 38:43.059
He's right. You can't admit...

38:43.103 --> 38:46.367
Diego...thank you.

38:46.411 --> 38:48.413
Yeah, man.

38:48.456 --> 38:54.070
♪♪

38:54.114 --> 38:57.117
You know, um...
[ Clears throat ]

38:57.160 --> 38:58.988
Back in grade school,
my teachers used to tell me

38:59.032 --> 39:01.469
that I was smart,
but I didn't apply myself.

39:01.513 --> 39:03.123
Mm.

39:03.166 --> 39:04.646
And that's what you're
trying to tell me, right?

39:04.690 --> 39:06.256
I need to apply myself?

39:06.300 --> 39:08.737
No. I'm trying to tell you
that you're arrogant,

39:08.781 --> 39:11.653
insubordinate,
and entitled.

39:11.697 --> 39:15.396
But...I got potential,
right?

39:15.440 --> 39:18.965
See you tomorrow, Doctor.

39:20.706 --> 39:23.404
All right.

39:23.448 --> 39:25.624
[ Door opens ]

39:25.667 --> 39:27.582
Hi.

39:34.502 --> 39:36.243
Can we talk?

39:36.286 --> 39:38.680
-So you can lie to me?
-I've never lied to you, Ariel.

39:38.724 --> 39:41.640
I always told you that Max is --
Not about Max. About us.

39:41.683 --> 39:44.817
Oh. I don't know what
you're talking about.

39:46.688 --> 39:48.864
You said this was home.

39:48.908 --> 39:52.433
You said that I'd always
be home with you.

39:52.477 --> 39:54.304
But now they're gonna
take me away again.

39:54.348 --> 39:55.915
Not if I can help it.
[ Sets cup down ]

39:55.958 --> 39:58.439
Can you promise that?
Can you guarantee it?

39:58.483 --> 40:01.660
Ariel, you remember when
we first met?

40:01.703 --> 40:03.662
Right after
your father's accident.

40:03.705 --> 40:06.534
I asked you
if you wanted it straight

40:06.578 --> 40:07.927
or if you wanted doctor talk.

40:07.970 --> 40:10.277
-I just want the truth.
-Okay, well, the truth is,

40:10.320 --> 40:14.281
I don't have
all the answers yet.

40:14.324 --> 40:16.718
It is very complicated.

40:16.762 --> 40:18.764
It's always complicated.

40:18.807 --> 40:22.507
My mom died, my dad died,

40:22.550 --> 40:23.986
and then my aunt
kicked me out.

40:24.030 --> 40:28.077
And then, Max died.

40:28.121 --> 40:30.776
When is it not gonna be
complicated?

40:32.386 --> 40:34.214
I love you.

40:35.563 --> 40:37.478
That's not complicated.

40:37.522 --> 40:40.612
But it's not enough.

40:40.655 --> 40:43.484
Because you're gonna be
taken from me, too.

40:43.528 --> 40:49.490
♪♪

40:49.534 --> 40:51.057
How we doing?

40:51.100 --> 40:52.754
You're not supposed
to be here.

40:52.798 --> 40:56.236
I didn't come as a doctor.
I came to apologize.

41:03.591 --> 41:05.637
So Jake's gone?

41:05.680 --> 41:09.075
Took me a few hours
to convince him, but yeah.

41:09.118 --> 41:12.339
He's finally gonna go
live his life.

41:12.382 --> 41:15.951
You know, Freud says that
we cast people in our lives

41:15.995 --> 41:19.172
to fix the things that we
couldn't get right before.

41:19.215 --> 41:23.829
[ Chuckles ]
He's no dummy. Freud.

41:23.872 --> 41:27.963
You know, maybe...

41:28.007 --> 41:31.401
your father knew your brother
wasn't strong enough.

41:31.445 --> 41:33.099
What do you mean?

41:33.142 --> 41:37.625
Maybe he sent him away
because he knew that...

41:37.669 --> 41:39.932
[ Sighs ] unlike you...

41:39.975 --> 41:41.934
[ Chuckles ]

41:41.977 --> 41:45.067
he wouldn't have been able
to handle it.

41:45.111 --> 41:49.898
No. Your father wasn't trying
to destroy your brother.

41:49.942 --> 41:54.424
He was...
trying to protect him.

41:54.468 --> 42:00.605
♪♪

42:00.648 --> 42:04.391
-May I?
-Oh, yeah. Be my guest.

42:04.434 --> 42:06.785
♪♪

42:06.828 --> 42:11.964
"My Long Ride Home.
Chapter One."

42:12.007 --> 42:13.748
"This morning,
like every morning,

42:13.792 --> 42:17.839
began with a promise
she made to herself."

42:17.883 --> 42:26.587
♪♪

42:26.631 --> 42:31.505
"Keeping it had always proved
impossible until today."

42:31.549 --> 42:37.467
♪♪

42:49.915 --> 42:51.917
♪♪
